<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-10080] Closure with type argument inference does not work as expected</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-10080</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have the following Groovy program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-groovy&quot;&gt;
@groovy.transform.CompileStatic
public &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Main {
  public static void main(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;[] args) {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; closure = {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Bar&amp;lt;&amp;gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Foo&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Long&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;());
    }
    closure().f.m(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; BigDecimal[0]) &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; doesn&apos;t work
&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// the following works
&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Bar&amp;lt;Foo&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Long&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; x = closure()
&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// x.f.m(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; BigDecimal[0]);
&lt;/span&gt;  }
}

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Foo&amp;lt;X&amp;gt; {
  void m(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt;[] x) {}
}


&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Bar&amp;lt;X&amp;gt; {
  X f;

  Bar(X f) {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.f = f;
  }
}

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Baz {}

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;ActualBehavior&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Actual Behavior&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The program does not compile, and I get the following error.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
org.codehaus.groovy.control.MultipleCompilationErrorsException: startup failed:
Main.groovy: 7: [Static type checking] - Cannot find matching method java.lang.&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt;#m(java.math.BigDecimal[]). Please check &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; the declared type is correct and &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; the method exists.
 @ line 7, column 5.
       closure().f.m(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; BigDecimal[0]) 
       ^

1 error

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;ExpectedBehavior&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Expected Behavior&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Compile successfully.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;AffectedVersion&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Affected Version&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This programs fails when compiled with the compiler from the master (commit: a8023b1b0d1d79800677ce2b4665ee3fb14688f4) and with 4.0.0-alpha-2.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
